data.title: Masters Of Jazz, Vol. 4
data.meta_description:
Masters Of Jazz, Vol. 4 by Ben Webster, released 17 March 2020

1. Johnny Come Lately
2. You'd Be so Nice to Come Home To
3. Stompy Jones
4. Cotton Tail
5. Going Home
6. Come Sunday
7. Our Blues
8. I Got It Bad
9. C Jam Blues
10. Star Dust
11. In a Mellotone
12. Sunday
13. Old Folks

Ben Webster came to Europe in 1964 and never returned to USA. He settled down in Denmark visited often Holland where he died in Amsterdam September 20, 1973. He is buried in Denmark. He made a lot of recordings with local musicians but also with visiting American Musicians. On this CD he plays with Teddy Wilson, Dexter Gordon, Sahib Shihab, Kenny Drew and Al Heath + local musicians. All the sessions are from Denmark and Finland where he played at the Pori Jazz Festival with Kenny Drew, NHØP and Al Heath.
data.text: Storyville Records is Europe’s oldest independent jazz label. It releases a rich variety of jazz, blues and related musical genres, often accompanied by authoritative notes and rare extras. This iconic label was founded in 1952 in Denmark and today continues to augment its historic catalogue of recordings made by American jazz and blues legends with new releases from contemporary jazz artists. ... more
